NORTHLAND COMPANY AND ITS SUBSIDIARIES (NORTHLAND) FROM CITIGROUP. ON OCTOBER 3, 2001, CITIGROUP CONTRIBUTED THE CAPITAL STOCK OF COMMERCIAL GUARANTY

CASUALTY INSURANCE COMPANY TO TPC. DURING APRIL 2000, TPC COMPLETED A CASH TENDER OFFER AND ACQUIRED ALL OF TRAVELERS INSURANCE GROUP HOLDINGS INC.S (TIGHI) OUTSTANDING SHARES OF COMMON STOCK THAT WERE NOT ALREADY OWNED BY TPC FOR

APPROXIMATELY $2.41 BILLION FINANCED BY A LOAN FROM CITIGROUP. ON MAY 31, 2000, TPC ACQUIRED THE SURETY BUSINESS OF RELIANCE GROUP HOLDINGS, INC. (RELIANCE SURETY). INCLUDES AMOUNTS RELATED TO NORTHLAND, COMMERCIAL GUARANTY CASUALTY, THE REMAINDER

