CUMULATIVE EFFECT OF CHANGES IN ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES, NET OF TAX (1) FOR THE YEAR ENDED DECEMBER 31, 2002 CONSISTED OF A LOSS OF $243 MILLION AS A RESULT OF A CHANGE IN ACCOUNTING

FOR GOODWILL AND OTHER INTANGIBLE ASSETS; AND (2) FOR THE YEAR ENDED DECEMBER 31, 2001 INCLUDED A GAIN OF $5 MILLION AS A RESULT OF A CHANGE IN ACCOUNTING FOR DERIVATIVE INSTRUMENTS AND HEDGING ACTIVITIES AND A LOSS OF $2 MILLION AS A RESULT OF A

CHANGE IN ACCOUNTING FOR SECURITIZED FINANCIAL ASSETS.

