PREMIUMS IN 2004 INCREASED $1.35 BILLION, OR 20%, OVER 2003, PRIMARILY REFLECTING THE IMPACT OF THE MERGER. BUSINESS RETENTION RATES REMAINED STRONG AND RENEWAL PRICE CHANGE INCREASES MODERATED TO THE LOW-SINGLE DIGIT LEVELS IN 2004. NEW BUSINESS

VOLUME DECLINED, HOWEVER, WHEN COMPARED WITH THE COMBINED NEW BUSINESS VOLUME OF SPC AND TPC IN 2003, REFLECTING THE INCREASINGLY COMPETITIVE MARKETPLACE AND THE IMPACT OF HIGHER PREMIUM FLOW IN 2003 ASSOCIATED WITH SEVERAL RENEWAL RIGHTS

