EMPLOYEE TERMINATION

AND RELOCATION COSTS CONSIST PRIMARILY OF SEVERANCE BENEFITS FOR WHICH PAYMENTS WILL BE SUBSTANTIALLY COMPLETED BY THE END OF 2006. COSTS TO EXIT LEASES INCLUDE REMAINING LEASE OBLIGATIONS ON PROPERTIES TO BE VACATED BY THE COMPANY AND ARE EXPECTED

TO BE FULLY PAID BY THE END OF 2007. OTHER EXIT COSTS INCLUDE THE REMAINING COSTS RELATED TO A REDUNDANT COMPUTER SOFTWARE CONTRACT WHICH ARE EXPECTED TO BE FULLY PAID BY THE END OF 2005. ADJUSTMENTS DURING 2004 PRIMARILY REPRESENT CHANGES IN THE

ORIGINAL ESTIMATE AS A RESULT OF NEW INFORMATION WHICH BECAME AVAILABLE TO THE COMPANY.

